1	their own heroic deeds and hapless fall
1	by doom of battle and complain that fate
1	free virtue should enthrall to force or chance 
1	their song was partial but the harmony
1	 what could it less when spirits immortal sing 
1	suspended hell and took with ravishment
1	the thronging audience in discourse more sweet
1	 for eloquence the soul song charms the sense 
1	others apart sat on a hill retired 
1	in thoughts more elevate and reasoned high
1	fixed fate free will foreknowledge absolute 
1	and found no end in wandering mazes lost 
1	of good and evil much they argued then 
1	of happiness and final misery 
1	passion and apathy and glory and shame 
1	vain wisdom all and false philosophy 
1	yet with a pleasing sorcery could charm
1	pain for a while or anguish and excite
1	fallacious hope or arm th obdured breast
1	with stubborn patience as with triple steel 
1	another part in squadrons and gross bands 
1	on bold adventure to discover wide
1	that dismal world if any clime perhaps
1	might yield them easier habitation bend
1	four ways their flying march along the banks
1	of four infernal rivers that disgorge
1	into the burning lake their baleful streams 
1	abhorred styx the flood of deadly hate 
1	sad acheron of sorrow black and deep 
1	cocytus named of lamentation loud
1	heard on the rueful stream fierce phlegeton 
1	whose waves of torrent fire inflame with rage 
1	far off from these a slow and silent stream 
1	lethe the river of oblivion rolls
1	her watery labyrinth whereof who drinks
1	forthwith his former state and being forgets 
1	forgets both joy and grief pleasure and pain 
1	beyond this flood a frozen continent
1	lies dark and wild beat with perpetual storms
1	of whirlwind and dire hail which on firm land
1	thaws not but gathers heap and ruin seems
