1	their lighter wings to whom these most adhere
1	he rules a moment chaos umpire sits 
1	and by decision more embroils the fray
1	by which he reigns next him high arbiter 
1	chance governs all into this wild abyss 
1	the womb of nature and perhaps her grave 
1	of neither sea nor shore nor air nor fire 
1	but all these in their pregnant causes mixed
1	confusedly and which thus must ever fight 
1	unless th almighty maker them ordain
1	his dark materials to create more worlds 
1	into this wild abyss the wary fiend
1	stood on the brink of hell and looked a while 
1	pondering his voyage for no narrow frith
1	he had to cross nor was his ear less pealed
1	with noises loud and ruinous to compare
1	great things with small than when bellona storms
