1	as in a cloudy chair ascending rides
1	audacious but that seat soon failing meets
1	a vast vacuity all unawares 
1	fluttering his pennons vain plumb down he drops
1	ten thousand fathom deep and to this hour
1	down had been falling had not by ill chance 
1	the strong rebuff of some tumultuous cloud 
1	instinct with fire and nitre hurried him
1	as many miles aloft that fury stayed 
1	quenched in a boggy syrtis neither sea 
1	nor good dry land nigh foundered on he fares 
1	treading the crude consistence half on foot 
1	half flying behoves him now both oar and sail 
1	as when a gryphon through the wilderness
1	with winged course o er hill or moory dale 
1	pursues the arimaspian who by stealth
1	had from his wakeful custody purloined
1	the guarded gold so eagerly the fiend
1	o er bog or steep through strait rough dense or rare 
1	with head hands wings or feet pursues his way 
1	and swims or sinks or wades or creeps or flies 
1	at length a universal hubbub wild
1	of stunning sounds and voices all confused 
