1	through the infinite host nor less for that
1	the flaming seraph fearless though alone
1	encompassed round with foes thus answered bold 
1	o alienate from god o spirit accursed 
1	forsaken of all good i see thy fall
1	determined and thy hapless crew involved
1	in this perfidious fraud contagion spread
1	both of thy crime and punishment henceforth
1	no more be troubled how to quit the yoke
1	of god s messiah those indulgent laws
1	will not be now vouchsafed other decrees
1	against thee are gone forth without recall 
1	that golden scepter which thou didst reject 
1	is now an iron rod to bruise and break
1	thy disobedience well thou didst advise 
1	yet not for thy advice or threats i fly
1	these wicked tents devoted lest the wrath
1	impendent raging into sudden flame 
1	distinguish not for soon expect to feel
1	his thunder on thy head devouring fire 
1	then who created thee lamenting learn 
1	when who can uncreate thee thou shalt know 
