1	gave them above their foes not to have sinned 
1	not to have disobeyed in fight they stood
1	unwearied unobnoxious to be pained
1	by wound though from their place by violence moved 
1	now night her course began and over heaven
1	inducing darkness grateful truce imposed 
1	and silence on the odious din of war 
1	under her cloudy covert both retired 
1	victor and vanquished on the foughten field
1	michael and his angels prevalent
1	encamping placed in guard their watches round 
1	cherubick waving fires on the other part 
1	satan with his rebellious disappeared 
1	far in the dark dislodged and void of rest 
1	his potentates to council called by night 
1	and in the midst thus undismayed began 
1	o now in danger tried now known in arms
1	not to be overpowered companions dear 
1	found worthy not of liberty alone 
1	too mean pretence but what we more affect 
1	honour dominion glory and renown 
1	who have sustained one day in doubtful fight 
1	 and if one day why not eternal days 
1	what heaven s lord had powerfullest to send
1	against us from about his throne and judged
1	sufficient to subdue us to his will 
1	but proves not so then fallible it seems 
1	of future we may deem him though till now
1	omniscient thought true is less firmly armed 
1	some disadvantage we endured and pain 
1	till now not known but known as soon contemned 
1	since now we find this our empyreal form
1	incapable of mortal injury 
1	imperishable and though pierced with wound 
1	soon closing and by native vigour healed 
1	of evil then so small as easy think
1	the remedy perhaps more valid arms 
1	weapons more violent when next we meet 
1	may serve to better us and worse our foes 
1	or equal what between us made the odds 
1	in nature none if other hidden cause
1	left them superiour while we can preserve
1	unhurt our minds and understanding sound 
1	due search and consultation will disclose 
1	he sat and in the assembly next upstood
1	nisroch of principalities the prime 
1	as one he stood escaped from cruel fight 
1	sore toiled his riven arms to havock hewn 
1	and cloudy in aspect thus answering spake 
1	deliverer from new lords leader to free
1	enjoyment of our right as gods yet hard
1	for gods and too unequal work we find 
1	against unequal arms to fight in pain 
1	against unpained impassive from which evil
1	ruin must needs ensue for what avails
1	valour or strength though matchless quelled with pain
1	which all subdues and makes remiss the hands
1	of mightiest sense of pleasure we may well
1	spare out of life perhaps and not repine 
1	but live content which is the calmest life 
1	but pain is perfect misery the worst
1	of evils and excessive overturns
1	all patience he who therefore can invent
1	with what more forcible we may offend
1	our yet unwounded enemies or arm
1	ourselves with like defence to me deserves
1	no less than for deliverance what we owe 
1	whereto with look composed satan replied 
1	not uninvented that which thou aright
1	believest so main to our success i bring 
1	which of us who beholds the bright surface
1	of this ethereous mould whereon we stand 
1	this continent of spacious heaven adorned
1	with plant fruit flower ambrosial gems and gold 
1	whose eye so superficially surveys
1	these things as not to mind from whence they grow
1	deep under ground materials dark and crude 
1	of spiritous and fiery spume till touched
1	with heaven s ray and tempered they shoot forth
1	so beauteous opening to the ambient light 
1	these in their dark nativity the deep
1	shall yield us pregnant with infernal flame 
1	which into hollow engines long and round 
1	thick rammed at the other bore with touch of fire
1	dilated and infuriate shall send forth
1	from far with thundering noise among our foes
1	such implements of mischief as shall dash
1	to pieces and o erwhelm whatever stands
1	adverse that they shall fear we have disarmed
1	the thunderer of his only dreaded bolt 
1	nor long shall be our labour yet ere dawn 
1	effect shall end our wish mean while revive 
1	abandon fear to strength and counsel joined
1	think nothing hard much less to be despaired 
1	he ended and his words their drooping cheer
1	enlightened and their languished hope revived 
1	the invention all admired and each how he
1	to be the inventer missed so easy it seemed
1	once found which yet unfound most would have thought
1	impossible yet haply of thy race
1	in future days if malice should abound 
1	some one intent on mischief or inspired
1	with devilish machination might devise
1	like instrument to plague the sons of men
1	for sin on war and mutual slaughter bent 
1	forthwith from council to the work they flew 
1	none arguing stood innumerable hands
1	were ready in a moment up they turned
1	wide the celestial soil and saw beneath
1	the originals of nature in their crude
1	conception sulphurous and nitrous foam
1	they found they mingled and with subtle art 
1	concocted and adusted they reduced
1	to blackest grain and into store conveyed 
1	part hidden veins digged up nor hath this earth
1	entrails unlike of mineral and stone 
1	whereof to found their engines and their balls
1	of missive ruin part incentive reed
1	provide pernicious with one touch to fire 
1	so all ere day spring under conscious night 
1	secret they finished and in order set 
1	with silent circumspection unespied 
1	now when fair morn orient in heaven appeared 
1	up rose the victor angels and to arms
