1	but firm battalion back with speediest sail
1	zophiel of cherubim the swiftest wing 
1	came flying and in mid air aloud thus cried 
1	arm warriours arm for fight the foe at hand 
1	whom fled we thought will save us long pursuit
1	this day fear not his flight so thick a cloud
1	he comes and settled in his face i see
1	sad resolution and secure let each
1	his adamantine coat gird well and each
1	fit well his helm gripe fast his orbed shield 
1	borne even or high for this day will pour down 
1	if i conjecture aught no drizzling shower 
1	but rattling storm of arrows barbed with fire 
1	so warned he them aware themselves and soon
1	in order quit of all impediment 
1	instant without disturb they took alarm 
1	and onward moved embattled when behold 
1	not distant far with heavy pace the foe
1	approaching gross and huge in hollow cube
1	training his devilish enginery impaled
1	on every side with shadowing squadrons deep 
1	to hide the fraud at interview both stood
1	a while but suddenly at head appeared
1	satan and thus was heard commanding loud 
1	vanguard to right and left the front unfold 
1	that all may see who hate us how we seek
1	peace and composure and with open breast
