1	our overture and turn not back perverse 
1	but that i doubt however witness heaven 
1	heaven witness thou anon while we discharge
1	freely our part ye who appointed stand
1	do as you have in charge and briefly touch
1	what we propound and loud that all may hear 
1	so scoffing in ambiguous words he scarce
1	had ended when to right and left the front
1	divided and to either flank retired 
1	which to our eyes discovered new and strange 
1	a triple mounted row of pillars laid
1	on wheels for like to pillars most they seemed 
1	or hollowed bodies made of oak or fir 
1	with branches lopt in wood or mountain felled 
1	brass iron stony mould had not their mouths
1	with hideous orifice gaped on us wide 
1	portending hollow truce at each behind
