1	second omnipotence two days are past 
1	two days as we compute the days of heaven 
1	since michael and his powers went forth to tame
1	these disobedient sore hath been their fight 
1	as likeliest was when two such foes met armed 
1	for to themselves i left them and thou knowest 
1	equal in their creation they were formed 
1	save what sin hath impaired which yet hath wrought
1	insensibly for i suspend their doom 
1	whence in perpetual fight they needs must last
1	endless and no solution will be found 
1	war wearied hath performed what war can do 
1	and to disordered rage let loose the reins
1	with mountains as with weapons armed which makes
1	wild work in heaven and dangerous to the main 
1	two days are therefore past the third is thine 
1	for thee i have ordained it and thus far
1	have suffered that the glory may be thine
1	of ending this great war since none but thou
1	can end it into thee such virtue and grace
1	immense i have transfused that all may know
1	in heaven and hell thy power above compare 
1	and this perverse commotion governed thus 
1	to manifest thee worthiest to be heir
1	of all things to be heir and to be king
1	by sacred unction thy deserved right 
