1	their nakedness with skins of beasts or slain 
1	or as the snake with youthful coat repaid 
1	and thought not much to clothe his enemies 
1	nor he their outward only with the skins
1	of beasts but inward nakedness much more 
1	opprobrious with his robe of righteousness 
1	arraying covered from his father s sight 
1	to him with swift ascent he up returned 
1	into his blissful bosom reassumed
1	in glory as of old to him appeased
1	all though all knowing what had passed with man
1	recounted mixing intercession sweet 
1	mean while ere thus was sinned and judged on earth 
1	within the gates of hell sat sin and death 
1	in counterview within the gates that now
1	stood open wide belching outrageous flame
1	far into chaos since the fiend passed through 
1	sin opening who thus now to death began 
1	o son why sit we here each other viewing
1	idly while satan our great author thrives
1	in other worlds and happier seat provides
1	for us his offspring dear it cannot be
1	but that success attends him if mishap 
1	ere this he had returned with fury driven
1	by his avengers since no place like this
1	can fit his punishment or their revenge 
1	methinks i feel new strength within me rise 
1	wings growing and dominion given me large
1	beyond this deep whatever draws me on 
1	or sympathy or some connatural force 
1	powerful at greatest distance to unite 
1	with secret amity things of like kind 
1	by secretest conveyance thou my shade
1	inseparable must with me along 
1	for death from sin no power can separate 
1	but lest the difficulty of passing back
1	stay his return perhaps over this gulf
1	impassable impervious let us try
1	adventurous work yet to thy power and mine
1	not unagreeable to found a path
1	over this main from hell to that new world 
1	where satan now prevails a monument
1	of merit high to all the infernal host 
1	easing their passage hence for intercourse 
1	or transmigration as their lot shall lead 
1	nor can i miss the way so strongly drawn
1	by this new felt attraction and instinct 
1	whom thus the meager shadow answered soon 
1	go whither fate and inclination strong 
1	leads thee i shall not lag behind nor err
1	the way thou leading such a scent i draw
1	of carnage prey innumerable and taste
1	the savour of death from all things there that live 
1	nor shall i to the work thou enterprisest
1	be wanting but afford thee equal aid 
1	so saying with delight he snuffed the smell
1	of mortal change on earth as when a flock
1	of ravenous fowl though many a league remote 
1	against the day of battle to a field 
1	where armies lie encamped come flying lured
1	with scent of living carcasses designed
1	for death the following day in bloody fight 
1	so scented the grim feature and upturned
1	his nostril wide into the murky air 
1	sagacious of his quarry from so far 
1	then both from out hell gates into the waste
1	wide anarchy of chaos damp and dark 
1	flew diverse and with power their power was great 
1	hovering upon the waters what they met
1	solid or slimy as in raging sea
1	tost up and down together crouded drove 
1	from each side shoaling towards the mouth of hell 
1	as when two polar winds blowing adverse
1	upon the cronian sea together drive
1	mountains of ice that stop the imagined way
1	beyond petsora eastward to the rich
1	cathaian coast the aggregated soil
1	death with his mace petrifick cold and dry 
1	as with a trident smote and fixed as firm
1	as delos floating once the rest his look
1	bound with gorgonian rigour not to move 
1	and with asphaltick slime broad as the gate 
1	deep to the roots of hell the gathered beach
1	they fastened and the mole immense wrought on
1	over the foaming deep high arched a bridge
1	of length prodigious joining to the wall
1	immoveable of this now fenceless world 
1	forfeit to death from hence a passage broad 
1	smooth easy inoffensive down to hell 
1	so if great things to small may be compared 
1	xerxes the liberty of greece to yoke 
1	from susa his memnonian palace high 
1	came to the sea and over hellespont
1	bridging his way europe with asia joined 
1	and scourged with many a stroke the indignant waves 
1	now had they brought the work by wonderous art
1	pontifical a ridge of pendant rock 
1	over the vexed abyss following the track
1	of satan to the self same place where he
1	first lighted from his wing and landed safe
1	from out of chaos to the outside bare
1	of this round world with pins of adamant
1	and chains they made all fast too fast they made
1	and durable and now in little space
1	the confines met of empyrean heaven 
1	and of this world and on the left hand hell
1	with long reach interposed three several ways
1	in sight to each of these three places led 
1	and now their way to earth they had descried 
1	to paradise first tending when behold 
1	satan in likeness of an angel bright 
1	betwixt the centaur and the scorpion steering
1	his zenith while the sun in aries rose 
1	disguised he came but those his children dear
1	their parent soon discerned though in disguise 
1	he after eve seduced unminded slunk
1	into the wood fast by and changing shape 
1	to observe the sequel saw his guileful act
1	by eve though all unweeting seconded
1	upon her husband saw their shame that sought
1	vain covertures but when he saw descend
1	the son of god to judge them terrified
1	he fled not hoping to escape but shun
1	the present fearing guilty what his wrath
1	might suddenly inflict that past returned
1	by night and listening where the hapless pair
1	sat in their sad discourse and various plaint 
1	thence gathered his own doom which understood
1	not instant but of future time with joy
1	and tidings fraught to hell he now returned 
1	and at the brink of chaos near the foot
1	of this new wonderous pontifice unhoped
1	met who to meet him came his offspring dear 
1	great joy was at their meeting and at sight
1	of that stupendous bridge his joy encreased 
1	long he admiring stood till sin his fair
1	enchanting daughter thus the silence broke 
1	o parent these are thy magnifick deeds 
1	thy trophies which thou viewest as not thine own 
1	thou art their author and prime architect 
1	for i no sooner in my heart divined 
1	my heart which by a secret harmony
1	still moves with thine joined in connexion sweet 
1	that thou on earth hadst prospered which thy looks
1	now also evidence but straight i felt 
1	though distant from thee worlds between yet felt 
1	that i must after thee with this thy son 
1	such fatal consequence unites us three 
1	hell could no longer hold us in our bounds 
1	nor this unvoyageable gulf obscure
1	detain from following thy illustrious track 
1	thou hast achieved our liberty confined
1	within hell gates till now thou us impowered
1	to fortify thus far and overlay 
1	with this portentous bridge the dark abyss 
1	thine now is all this world thy virtue hath won
1	what thy hands builded not thy wisdom gained
1	with odds what war hath lost and fully avenged
1	our foil in heaven here thou shalt monarch reign 
1	there didst not there let him still victor sway 
1	as battle hath adjudged from this new world
1	retiring by his own doom alienated 
1	and henceforth monarchy with thee divide
1	of all things parted by the empyreal bounds 
1	his quadrature from thy orbicular world 
1	or try thee now more dangerous to his throne 
1	whom thus the prince of darkness answered glad 
1	fair daughter and thou son and grandchild both 
1	high proof ye now have given to be the race
1	of satan for i glory in the name 
1	antagonist of heaven s almighty king 
1	amply have merited of me of all
1	the infernal empire that so near heaven s door
1	triumphal with triumphal act have met 
1	mine with this glorious work and made one realm 
1	hell and this world one realm one continent
1	of easy thorough fare therefore while i
1	descend through darkness on your road with ease 
1	to my associate powers them to acquaint
1	with these successes and with them rejoice 
1	you two this way among these numerous orbs 
1	all yours right down to paradise descend 
1	there dwell and reign in bliss thence on the earth
1	dominion exercise and in the air 
1	chiefly on man sole lord of all declared 
1	him first make sure your thrall and lastly kill 
1	my substitutes i send ye and create
1	plenipotent on earth of matchless might
1	issuing from me on your joint vigour now
1	my hold of this new kingdom all depends 
1	through sin to death exposed by my exploit 
1	if your joint power prevail the affairs of hell
1	no detriment need fear go and be strong 
1	so saying he dismissed them they with speed
1	their course through thickest constellations held 
1	spreading their bane the blasted stars looked wan 
1	and planets planet struck real eclipse
