1	that proud excuse yet him not thy election 
1	but natural necessity begot 
1	god made thee of choice his own and of his own
1	to serve him thy reward was of his grace 
1	thy punishment then justly is at his will 
1	be it so for i submit his doom is fair 
1	that dust i am and shall to dust return 
1	o welcome hour whenever why delays
1	his hand to execute what his decree
1	fixed on this day why do i overlive 
1	why am i mocked with death and lengthened out
