1	which to his eye discovers unaware
1	the goodly prospect of some forein land
1	first seen or some renownd metropolis
1	with glistering spires and pinnacles adornd 
1	which now the rising sun guilds with his beams 
1	such wonder seis d though after heaven seen 
1	the spirit maligne but much more envy seis d
1	at sight of all this world beheld so faire 
1	round he surveys and well might where he stood
1	so high above the circling canopie
1	of nights extended shade from eastern point
