1	through the calm firmament but up or downe
1	by center or eccentric hard to tell 
1	or longitude where the great luminarie
1	alooff the vulgar constellations thick 
1	that from his lordly eye keep distance due 
1	dispenses light from farr they as they move
1	thir starry dance in numbers that compute
1	days months and years towards his all chearing lamp
1	turn swift their various motions or are turnd
1	by his magnetic beam that gently warms
1	the univers and to each inward part
1	with gentle penetration though unseen 
1	shoots invisible vertue even to the deep 
