1	my dissolution michael repli d 
1	though bent on speed so heer the archangel paus d
1	betwixt the world destroy d and world restor d 
1	if adam aught perhaps might interpose 
1	then with transition sweet new speech resumes 
1	thus thou hast seen one world begin and end 
1	and man as from a second stock proceed 
1	much thou hast yet to see but i perceave
1	thy mortal sight to faile objects divine
1	must needs impaire and wearie human sense 
1	henceforth what is to com i will relate 
1	thou therefore give due audience and attend 
1	this second sours of men while yet but few 
1	and while the dread of judgement past remains
1	fresh in thir mindes fearing the deitie 
1	with some regard to what is just and right
1	shall lead thir lives and multiplie apace 
1	labouring the soile and reaping plenteous crop 
1	corn wine and oyle and from the herd or flock 
1	oft sacrificing bullock lamb or kid 
1	with large wine offerings pour d and sacred feast
1	shal spend thir dayes in joy unblam d and dwell
1	long time in peace by families and tribes
1	under paternal rule till one shall rise
1	of proud ambitious heart who not content
1	with fair equalitie fraternal state 
1	will arrogate dominion undeserv d
1	over his brethren and quite dispossess
1	concord and law of nature from the earth 
